	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64483211"><p><span class="substr"> </span> <em>Power yes, power you can use for charging your car no</em> </p><p>This isn't rocket surgery. How about someone invents a device whereby they can put a car charging port into the lamp posts so that people can charge. They could use names like "ubitricity" for "ubiquitous electricity" or "chargy" which is cute and lets you use a domain like char.gy. To make life easier registered the domains for you:</p><p> <a href="https://ubitricity.com/" title="ubitricity.com">https://ubitricity.com/</a> [ubitricity.com] </p><p> <a href="https://char.gy/" title="char.gy">https://char.gy/</a> [char.gy] </p><p>Blatant sarcasm aside, this is what on street charging can actually look like in a ci</p></div>
	</div>

