	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64482731"><p><div class="quote"><p>EVs are significantly more expensive than equivalent gasoline-powered cars. If you hold your head just right, and you can charge from home, you can sort of pretend that the savings in fuel costs justifies the higher purchase price.</p></div><p>Here's a <a href="https://www.caranddriver.com/shopping-advice/a32494027/ev-vs-gas-cheaper-to-own/" title="caranddriver.com">3 year TCO comparison</a> [caranddriver.com] that has EVs and ICE cars coming in at about the same.
</p><p>
That's for the first 3 years; if you hold onto the EV longer, the decreased energy and maintenance costs will continue to make them cheaper.
</p><p>
On top of that, as EV tech continues to improve, their cost will come down and reliability will go up (maintenance costs will come down even further).</p></div>
	</div>

