	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64482987"><p>It's false that LFPs can't be ignited. They are much, much harder to ignite, but they can still burn. They are also much, much easier to put out because NCM electrolyte releases oxygen when heated and LFP doesn't (which is also a large part of why they are less likely to combust) but they are also still toxic when burning and non-trivial to extinguish. I am very pro-LFP because they are better about all of these things than NCM, and support more and more EVs being made with them, but I do still hope for sup<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64482987">

