			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64482677"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64482677"><p>For example, the EV tax credit rules <a href="https://www.irs.gov/credits-deductions/credits-for-new-clean-vehicles-purchased-in-2023-or-after" title="irs.gov">https://www.irs.gov/credits-de...</a> [irs.gov] exclude vehicles over a certain weight, and over a certain price, and if your income is too high, you don't qualify, and the vehicle must be assembled in the US. There are a bunch of other rules that have nothing to do with the desire to transition to "clean EVs." If I'm a vehicle manufacturer, why shouldn't I be able to protest some of these provisions, without being labeled "anti-EV"?</p></div>
	</div>

